Neotropical. 
<collectingCountry id="F342762D904C6A1E559FCEDCD57D81C7" box="[505,590,188,212]" name="Mexico" pageId="4">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(Tabasco, Oaxaca, Guerrero).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F6536904C6A1E54A1CE80D62C800E" pageId="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEA36BD904C6A1E54A1CE80D62C800E" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,463]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="B921EAAF904C6A1E54A1CE80D67D81EB" bold="true" box="[199,334,224,248]" pageId="4">Etymology.</emphasis>
We name this species after Ms. Patricia E. Gomora Rosales, for her support of our work through many years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F6536904C6A1E54A1CF47D6E980DC" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEA36BD904C6A1E54A1CF47D6E980DC" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,463]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="B921EAAF904C6A1E54A1CF47D6768053" bold="true" box="[199,325,295,320]" pageId="4">Discussion</emphasis>
. This new species is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3E904C6A1E5682CF48D3BD802C" authority="Cook, 1956" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1956" box="[740,1166,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Abrhexosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="B921EAAF904C6A1E5682CF48D4DA8053" box="[740,1001,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="4">Abrhexosa panamensis</emphasis>
(Cook, 
<number id="3D9D249A904C6A1E502DCF47D3B4802C" box="[1099,1159,295,319]" pageId="4" value="1956.0">1956</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from which it may be distinguished by posterior margin deeply emarginated of the sternite 
<number id="3D9D249A904C6A1E57FECF2DD4958077" box="[920,934,333,356]" pageId="4" value="7.0">7</number>
and male genitalia with an additional simple and setose process, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3E904C6A1E566FCF10D582809B" box="[521,689,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Abrhexosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis id="B921EAAF904C6A1E566FCF10D529809B" box="[521,538,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="4">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B921EAAF904C6A1E564BCF11D582809B" box="[557,689,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="4">panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the posterior emargination of sternite 
<number id="3D9D249A904C6A1E501ECF10D3B58094" box="[1144,1158,368,391]" pageId="4" value="7.0">7</number>
with a shallow median posterior emargination and has no setose process. The characters of aedeagus, parameres and tergite 
<number id="3D9D249A904C6A1E5140CFF4D20780BF" box="[1318,1332,404,428]" pageId="4" value="9.0">9</number>
are very similar in both these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
